Anyway, thatâ€™s my take. I really enjoyed the film. It was a lot of fun and the soundtrack is great. 

Fin. https://t.co/C3CYoxOdyB
Itâ€™s about being disrespected by Thor, and being tired that people put their faith in heroes (who have done things and acted in peopleâ€™s interests) not gods (who havenâ€™t).

You telling me that a Zeus that cares about humans is going to just stand by and let Thanos do what he did? 

Nah, he didnâ€™t care. He could put on a show for the other gods and be happy. Itâ€™s only when he gets one upped by Thor that he cares, but then itâ€™s not about people.
Now, did I particularly like Russel Croweâ€™s acting? Not really. His Greek accent was unconvincing. But, the character did what we probably should have expected a powerful god to do in this film.
Phase 4 has sort of hit home that there are some powerful entities in the MCU that are either 1) unconcerned about humans (the gods) or downright hostile to them (celestials).

So, when Zeus shows up, who is expecting him to be like, â€œHades yes, Thor, I will help you. Letâ€™s smite this dude!â€ 

I donâ€™t know comic book Zeus. I assume heâ€™s crazy powerful and awesome. But the Zeus of this film? Heâ€™s not going to be like that.

That god threw fruit at this poor guy, who suffered but kept the faith. And this god is like, â€œlol, thatâ€™s low key hilarious that your daughter died and you thought I would do something about itâ€

And uhâ€¦thatâ€™s the point? Like the whole point is that the gods have stopped caring about people and only care about themselves.

Did you not see the first ten minutes of the movie where a god literally laughs at one of his devoted followers who just buried his kid?

And Zeusâ€¦well, he sucks. He puts in a big show but he doesnâ€™t really do anything.

And there are people who have watched it that are mad about this. â€œZeus is lame!â€ â€œI canâ€™t believe they did that to Zeus.â€

So, in the film, Thor and friends go to the city of the gods (I know it has a name, but I forget it. Something like Omniscity, because comic pun) and Zeus gets hyped up. Like Thor is so stoked to see him and is like, â€œMy dudes. Zeus!â€
Hey, so, Iâ€™m going to tweet a bit about #ThorLoveAndThunder so spoilers, but I want to talk about one of the criticisms of the film that Iâ€™ve seen.
